sentences: Ángela Aguilar Álvarez (born October 8, 2003) is a Mexican-American singer.
Aguilar gained notable recognition after performing "La Llorona" at the 19th Annual Latin Grammy Awards in 2018.
Her debut solo studio album, Primero Soy Mexicana (2018), was met with critical acclaim and success.
Ángela Aguilar Álvarez was born to Pepe Aguilar and Aneliz Álvarez-Alcala in Los Angeles, California on October 8, 2003, while her father was on tour.
In July 2018, Aguilar partnered with Voto Latino to encourage more Latino Americans to vote in American elections.
In 2012, at just nine years old, Aguilar released Nueva Tradición, alongside her brother, Leonardo.
In 2016, Aguilar participated in the BBC 100 Woman festival in Mexico City.
In January 2018, Aguilar and her family launched an equestrian-musical style tour dubbed "Jaripeo Sin Fronteras".
On March 2, 2018, Aguilar released her first solo album, Primero Soy Mexicana, produced by her father, Pepe.
Aguilar performed the album's first single, "Tu Sangre en Mi Cuerpo" at the 2018 Premios Tu Mundo.
On September 20, 2018, Aguilar was nominated for Best New Artist and her album, Primero Soy Mexicana was nominated for Best Ranchero/Mariachi Album at the 19th Annual Latin Grammy Awards.
On December 7, 2018, Aguilar's album Primero Soy Mexicana, was nominated for a Grammy Award for Best Regional Mexican Music Album.
On April 3, 2019, Aguilar was named the Artistic and Cultural Ambassador of Zacatecas, Mexico by Mayor Ulises Mejía Haro.
On May 21, 2019, Aguilar was nominated for three awards at the 2019 Premios Juventud.

On July 23, 2019, Aguilar released an exclusive cover performance of "Shallow" on the Recording Academy's YouTube page, with permission from the songwriter, Lady Gaga.
On January 31, 2020, Aguilar released a tribute album to American singer, Selena, titled Baila Esta Cumbia.
